abstract: Arkansas. Cotton-Seventy five per cent is planted, and it is expected that planting will be finished by the 10th inst., two weeks earlier than last year. During the latter part of April severe rain-storms set in, extending over the north-eastern portion, necessitating replanting in many cases. Labor is doing well. The condition of the crop is good and advanced. There is a heavy rise in the Arkansas River, but no overflow is apprehended.

His oration was delivered in the Broadway Methodist Church, after the ceremony of decorating the graves, which was attended with much more form and display than usual, attracting a large crowd of people. Gen. Kilpatrick pictured the day as a nation's day of mourning, on which thousands all over the land were assembled in sacred spots.
